genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica occitana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica occitana is a traditional music genre from the Occitan regions of France, Italy, and Spain. It features a mix of folk instruments and vocal harmonies, often sung in the Occitan language. The music is known for its lively rhythms and storytelling elements, with many songs focusing on local legends and historical events.
